<statement><div><p>Consider the complex number <m>z = {3} {+} {5}\cdot i</m>.</p>
<p>1. Write <m>z</m> in polar or trigonometric form. Give the modulus in exact form and the argument correct to <m>2</m> decimal places within your answer.</p>
<p><m>z = </m> <fillin characters="18" name="ans1"/>  </p>
<p>2. Write <m>z</m> in exponential form. Give the modulus and the argument in exact form. Recall that <m>e^k</m> is entered as <c>%e^(k)</c>.</p>
